The paper discusses the use of Inductive Logic Programming (ILP) for feature construction and its application in predictive modeling. This falls under the domain of machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG and cs.AI the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of a distributed approach for feature construction, which involves networked computational units, making cs.DB and cs.DC likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper discusses the practical applications of the approach, which could fall under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
